body_html: SpatialBN is caffe2 op, which is the implementation of BatchNormalization in Caffe2. According to your error message, it seems the input X's dimension is >5 or <3, which is not supported by the implementation in SpatialBN. You can compare your shufflenet with the one in our model zoo: https://github.com/onnx/models/tree/master/shufflenet

body: `SpatialBN` is caffe2 op, which is the implementation of BatchNormalization in Caffe2. According to your error message, it seems the input `X`'s dimension is >5 or <3, which is not supported by the implementation in SpatialBN. You can compare your shufflenet with the one in our model zoo: https://github.com/onnx/models/tree/master/shufflenet
